name: Brother, Can You Spare Two Dimes?
Powdered Toast Man vs Waffle Woman

deck: Bulma and Goku endeavour to help poor old lost Turtle find his way back to the sea. As a token of his thanks, he urges them to wait by the sea while he goes off and retrieves his master...a seemingly frail and wizened old man -- with a streak of the pervert about him!
description:
Original Title: 亀仙人のキント雲 (Kamesen'nin no Kinto'un)

Continuing immediately on from the last episode, Goku and Bulma with Turtle in tow's paths are interrupted by the sudden appearance of a large --and hungry!-- Bear Bandit. Wishing to make Turtle his supper, Goku steps in and quickly dispatches the bear, allowing them to continue onwards to the seaside.

As they arrive on the beach, Turtle pleads with them to remain on the sand while he swims off to retrieve his master. Goku & Bulma comply, and Turtle reappears carrying on his back the venerable Master Roshi! After Turtle & Roshi spend a few minutes pondering about how they'll reward Goku only, to which Bulma protests, Roshi decides to gift Goku with the mystical cloud th Flying Nimbus, a unique object in that only those of true and pure heart can be allowed to sit upon it and fly anywhere. Master Roshi tries to demonstrate this; but soon enough falls through the cloud! Bulma tries her luck too, but meets with similar results.

While Master Roshi joins the gang on the beach, the tenacious Emperor Pilaf, together with his trusted henchmen Mia & Shu has traced another Dragon Ball to Kami House; the humble pink florescent home of Turtle Hermit Roshi. Back on landfall, Bulma becomes aware that Roshi has in fact a Dragon Ball hanging around his neck, and in a flirtacious act eventually convinces him to hand it over.

Both parties then split up; Goku & Bulma head home, while Roshi & Turtle return to their island, removing the ruffian emperor and his ilk in the process.
name: The Nimbus Cloud of Roshi

description: Peter is beginning to give up. He's tired of Spider-Man being called a menace when he tries to help. But when he receives a letter from Spidey's #1 fan, Tina, he decides to give Spider-Man one last swing.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 2: Make a Wish

description: Dr. Octopus has captured Spider-Man and erases his memory. Now, it's up to Taina to save him.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 3: Attack of the Octobot

description:
After an explosion at Oscorp Industries, Norman Osborn has gone missing. Soon after, a menace called the Green Goblin appears and starts kidnapping the chair members of Oscorp's board.

Note: Mendel Stromm is renamed Wardel Stromm in this episode.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 4: Enter the Green Goblin

description: Robert, a former troublemaker, has been trying to help his mother with her business and her illness. But when a new gang, lead by Big-Wheel, threaten them, Robert takes matters into his own hands.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 5: The Rocket Racer

description: When Peter Parker is framed for treason, the only help he has is from Matt Murdock, both as his lawyer and as the superhero Daredevil.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 6: Framed

description: Satisfied that Spider-Man is on his side, Daredevil joins forces with him to clear Peter's name and bring the Kingpin to justice.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 7: The Man Without Fear

description: Alistair Smyth is planning on betraying the Kingpin. But when Kingpin finds out, he hires Landon to inject his mutation formula into Smythe. Now Smythe has become the Ultimate Spider Slayer.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 8: The Ultimate Slayer

description: Tombstone, one of Silvermane's former henchmen, has returned and is threatening to ruin the life of childhood pal, Robbie, if he doesn't destroy the story that he's about to print about the Silvermane family.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 9: Tombstone

description: Baron Mordo is back. He is planning to steal Tony Stark's technology on dimensions so that he can bring the being known as Dormammu to Earth. But he will also need the help of Spider-Man's greatest enemy: Venom.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 10: Venom Returns

description: The Venom symbiote has produced a new symbiote, attaching itself to serial killer Cletus Kasady to give birth to Carnage. As Venom's replacement, Carnage helps Mordo with his plans. Now, Spider-Man must team up with Venom and Iron-Man.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 11: Carnage

description: After Tony Stark eliminates Dr. Ohn's research on dimensions, Ohn makes a deal with the Kingpin. After a malfunction in his new lab, Ohn is sucked into another dimension and becomes a powerful being, known as The Spot.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 12: The Spot

description: The Hobgoblin returns, this time with the time dilation accelerator. The Kingpin turns to Norman Osborn, who created the Hobgoblin, for help. But when the Green Goblin takes over, it's war.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 13: Goblin Wars

description: Famed Lawndale High quarterback, Tommy Sherman, dies in a freak accident while visiting his alma mater, prompting Jane to avoid Daria for a while and everyone else to dub Daria "The Misery Chick".
name: The Misery Chick

description: The Green Goblin has found out Spider-Man's true identity. Now he's after Mary Jane, Peter's girlfriend.
name: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 14: The Turning Point
So It's Come to This: A Simpsons Clip Show
